  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Education Gift to 9 Girls at Hope School, Kenya</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Orphans and Vulnerable Girl&apos;s in Africa face various hurdles on their path to education. Culture and tradition often keeps them at home while their brothers go to school. Some girls are forced to marry when they are as young as 13 in exchange for a few cows. If a girl convinces her family to send her to a &quot;free&quot; government school, she often cannot go because she lacks the funds for a uniform or supplies. Hope School is a social enterprise giving quality basic education to poor children.</narrative>
  </description>
